qas.question: What islands are not geographically part of Southeast Asia

plausible_answers.text: Eastern Bangladesh and the Seven Sister States of India

qas.question: What islands are not culturally or geographically part of Southeast Asia?
What part of New Guinea is not part of Southeast Asia?

context: <a0_0><b3_0>The Andaman and Nicobar Islands<a0_0/> of India<b3_0/> are geographically considered part of Southeast Asia. <a1_0><b4_0>Eastern Bangladesh and the Seven Sister States of India<b4_0/><a1_0/> are culturally part of Southeast Asia and sometimes considered both South Asian and Southeast Asian. The Seven Sister States of India are also geographically part of Southeast Asia.[citation needed] The rest of the island of New Guinea which is not part of Indonesia, namely, <a2_0><b5_0>Papua New Guinea<b5_0/>, is sometimes included so are Palau, Guam, and the Northern Mariana Islands<a2_0/>, which were all part of the Spanish East Indies.[citation needed]
